I have improved the error handling for the OCR Tool to provide more specific, actionable feedback to users when text extraction fails.
Key Improvements:
Specific Error Categorization: The tool now distinguishes between different failure types:
Network Errors: Detects if the user is offline or if the OCR engine fails to download from the CDN.
Engine Initialization Errors: Specifically identifies issues with the Tesseract worker or script loading.
File/Format Issues: Detects potential corruption or unsupported image formats.
Empty Detection: Provides a helpful message if an image is processed successfully but no text is found (e.g., due to low contrast or blur).
Retry Mechanism: Added a prominent "Try Again" button within the error state, allowing users to re-trigger the recognition process without having to re-upload their file.
Enhanced UI Feedback:
The error display is now a more detailed card with a clear title and descriptive message.
Added a helpful "Pro Tip" hint during the processing phase to manage user expectations.
Added a pre-check for internet connectivity to provide immediate feedback before attempting to load the OCR engine.
These changes ensure that users are not left with generic "Failed" messages and instead understand exactly why an error occurred and how they might fix it.
